The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Jessop amp; Co Ltd has reported an 11 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 11.07 crore for 2006-07. The total income increased to Rs 83.92 crore during 2006-07 compared with Rs 78.67 crore a year ago. The company has declared a dividend of 10 per cent for the year. Jessop chairman P. K. Ruia said wagon production grew by 153 per cent during the year. We hope to generate about 10 per cent of our total revenue from the steel segment, he said. 

 Real estate developer Unitech has posted a nearly 15-fold growth in consolidated profit after tax at Rs 1,305.49 crore for the year ended March 31, against Rs 87.64 crore in the same period a year ago. The consolidated total income rose to Rs 3,388.36 crore for the year ended March 31, compared with Rs 954.50 crore in the year-ago period. The board has recommended a bonus issue of 1:1.

 Crompton Greaves will acquire Ireland-based Microsol Holdings Ltd for an enterprise value of around 10.50 million euros. This acquisition will increase the companys strengths in high-end engineering and sub-station automation capabilities, a company statement said. 

 Kalpataru Power Transmission Ltd has reported an 80 per cent increase in gross turnover for 2006-07 at Rs 1,567 crore against Rs 871 crore a year ago. The profit before tax was up 130 per cent to Rs 216 crore from Rs 94 crore in the previous year. The board has recommended an annual dividend of 75 per cent compared with 50 per cent in the previous year.

 Glenmark Pharmaceuticals has completed the Phase I clinical trials for GRC 6211, a pain reliever, and plans to launch the molecule in 2011. 

 The State Bank of Bikaner amp; Jaipur (sbbj) has increased the interest rates on fixed deposits. Term deposits of less than 15 lakh with a one-year tenure will now get an interest rate of 9.50 per cent against 8.25 per cent earlier. 

 The SBI has tied up with Maruti Udyog Ltd for a real-time processing of car loans. The online system will connect Maruti dealers with the retail assets central processing centre for instant transmission of the car loan application details to the centre.

 Cambridge Technology Enterprises will acquire US-based Comcreation Inc for $3.50 million. The board has approved the acquisition. The company is completing the formalities of the acquisition.

 Airtel has launched a voice chat service on fixed lines. The service will help customers chat with other Airtel mobile and fixed line customers.

